rComments: Great teacher, explains things very well. One downside is he speaks in a monotonic manner, can be difficult to stay focused.
ECE241 was one of my favourite courses of second year. Chow is a great lecturer and explains the concepts really clearly.
he's a nice prof, great sense of humour,  and always happy to answer questions.  The course was challenging, but I had a lot of fun

I didn't know much about the prof before taking the course and was scared from the comments and ratings that I saw/heard. I was glad to find out the Prof is pretty good. He knows the material and explains it well and in a clear fashion. Midterm results were low (60's) but in all honesty they weren't hard. It's just very easy to make mistakes.
